  "StockRole": "Superheavy",
  "YangsThoughts": "The Smilodon is a 110-ton line BattleMech fielded by the Minnesota Tribe, produced by Independence Weaponry as a dependable frontline brawler. Named after the prehistoric saber-toothed predator, the Smilodon symbolizes brutal efficiency and predatory focus—traits the Tribe values in its martial tradition. Its design draws inspiration from the Ebon Jaguar, sharing a low-slung, forward-thrusting posture and a menacing profile suited for battlefield intimidation. While lacking the advanced modularity of an OmniMech, the Smilodon is built for sustained frontline engagement. It uses Ferro-Silk armor—a lightweight, steel-polymer lattice developed by Northern Meshworks—trading some durability for weight savings to support heavier weapons in line with the Tribe’s focus on overwhelming offensive capability. The Smilodon stands as a testament to the Tribe’s doctrine of overwhelming force and their refusal to abandon classic battle-tested principles.",
